INFRASTRUCTURE ARCHITECTURE, LIVE ENVIRONMENT
AS IS 2015
Status: Draft and Incomplete (in many cases speculative!)
Author: Nikki Rogers, Date: June 2015

INFRASTRUCTURE ARCHITECTURE TO BE 2016
Status: Draft and Incomplete (in many cases speculative! Noting that all change requires resources - investment.)
Author: Nikki Rogers
Date: June 2015
No corporate solution, USB's, disks, Dropbox etc variously used
No corporate solution. On premise HPC too expensive. VM's in the Cloud currently not efficient enough/too expensive - hybrid solution possible?

Does OneDrive give sufficient quota for academics and if not would we be able to provide SAN storage to meet their needs? Also sharepoint.
On premise fileshares also still needed for certain applications? - yes
Tactical Replacement with Tintri planned for the interim
Need to retain any SAN?

Or is it a NAS-SAN hybrid?
At June 2015 the NAS is Under migration now (EMC support ended Jan 2015), finalise end July

Locations referred to:
FR1 - B-Block, 2B12, UWE Main Campus
FR2 - B-Block DMZ, UWE Main Campus
FR3 - Building 640 downstairs, ITS, UWE Business Park
Would Prefer Virtual host in FR3. Vulnerability on Master Service and Nexsan FR3
SQL Server backup
Only a single Tape library, about 4-5 years
Approx 60
Access databases, MySQL and prob standalone SQL servers exist outside of ITS (e.g. FET)

Mirrored architecture predates the HA SQL Server Group architecture (approx 10). Some of these implementations are marked for retirement e.g. Agresso. We are moving apps gradually over to the HA group implementation. Need to do EOL because Windows 2003 gone EOL

Latest and preferred approach: One HA group per application Service for SQL Sever platform
Approx half a dozen groups like this, and increasing
Supports ISIS, represents diversity
Standalone and SQL Server cluster due EOL Summer 2015
Filestore - depends on VMWare, using Tintri for storage
1 external supplier requires virtualised Windows XP
And note SQL Server 2016 coming and we should aim to move to that

Tintri for file server support only?
Considering more Tintri's?

Only single tape library, 4-5 years
Also other Storage exists for FET, but withdrawal of NAS will remove the user data, but system backups will still remain
Backup to standalone servers, mirrored using DFS, between the two datacentres
Unused? Legacy. Solaris used in the main
HP Intel Servers for VM's (Older Oracle Sun's being phased out - they have been the hosting linux platform until now)
Nick Eaton - check with him

Ask Alan Price - FET IT - FET IT Mac labs, Matt Welch - Mac support, based in FET
Think Casper is management software re installing software updates and patches, implementing group policies etc? - ask Alan
NB Bower Ashton - lots of Macs
Staff Mac usage: Printing, Stationery and Marketing often have Macs for work - pretty standalone
There's an aspect of Support for BYOD as well.

Looking to buy replacement hosts and upgrade to Solaris 11
Looking to consolidate 4 Solaris VMware platforms on to one

All LIbrary services, ISIS, MyUWE portal, Consolidation Servers for www. are on Solaris too - so could show more platforms.
MyUWE environment has similar environment to ISIS - has 4 servers, utlises the NAS
Library services - some of - are being moved on to Consolidation Servers. (see Nick Eaton).
Plan: gradually moving Library - some of - to Consolidation Servers. Currently a shared service with Bath Spa (contact: lawrence), hosted and managed by UWE
Plan: MyUWE -> linux platform and SAN (and uses NAS not SAN currently)
NB web was put on CMS, internal web on Intranet, www is now a set of redirects - via consolidation servers.
Also couple of remaining standalone, legacy Solaris boxes

Next steps: analyse to show storage capacity, resilience, single points of failure and build in the application layer over the top to show which corporate applications depend on which infrastructure services
Aim: end of life
Target: reduced diversity
Reduce number of standalones in favour of VMs?
Upgrade to Solaris 11 and consider replacement of Solaris wholesale (can Library, Web, Student Admin System apps be moved?)

? There is a network roadmap.
Update services - not known
Monitoring services - a unified view of service monitoring is the goal, we need to consider the strategy of monitoring services across both Cloud and on premise corporate systems
Licensed SQL server hosts

Arkivum - about to license, machine here, backed up to Cloud. Tape Library.
Initially for Bristol Robotics Lab, FET, to be rolled out Uni-wide eventually. Research Data sets, that will be retained for 20 yrs.
Arkivum links with ePrints - integrated.

Keep some NAS, educate users as to where put personal files, where to work collaboratively. Assess possibility of shared folders provided by OneDrive for Business (MS Azure shared drives, based in EU, agreed with Janet). Avoid Dropbox. Beware data security and incident management. Also syncing capability
If Cloud-based Linux VMs are not efficient enough for a minority of taught causes (e.g. Computer Science) then continue to provide Linux labs on premise as a special case
Talk to greg marsh about unix servers we support
